<br>
/em casts Social Skills Spiral of Al'Kabor<br>
<br>
Damn, just as crappy a spell as the rest of them.  <br>
<br>
Truth is, both sides are right, when they finally get around to the point of the topic, because both sides are, for the most part, arguing separate points.  Beryl extols the value of AoE grouping and quad kiting, and picks on those who still seek some form of group enhancement.  Those who prefer, for whatever reason, to stick with regular groups insist that wizards need something to make them more desirable to regular groups.  Both sides talk as if they're discussing the same topic, but really they are not.<br>
<br>
As for myself (lvl 45 at this point):  I very quickly grew to love quad kiting (never thought it would happen), but I prefer grouping to soloing.  I like to socialize with new people, and downtime when quadding is annoying.  I would love to do more AoE, but I'm not sure of the practicality of it at my level, and finding people of this level interested in trying the tactic is very difficult.  I will, however, be reading the thread Beryl mentioned.<br>
<br>
So mostly I group, and I find that in most circumstances I end up filling the 6th slot when no other class is available.  So I would like to see *something* to make us more desirable.  It could be any number of things, really, I'm not looking for much.  I don't need to outdamage rogues or become a buff slave.  But I am looking for something.  This won't, presumably, displace another class as Beryl warns, and perhaps it wouldn't be the panacea that so many look for (with unreasonable ideals, it often seems).  But I think it would be balancing.<br>
<br>
I disagree that all classes should be equally attractive to groups.  All classes should simply be attractive, period.  The game is well past the point where equal attractiveness can be implemented, and even were we discussing beta, I think I'd disagree with Grimstaff's point.<br>
<br>
Caracatan Stormforge<br>
Rambling Devotee of Solusek Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/01 7:37:30 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some thoughts on grouping...</span><hr size=1> Never seen the Mage pet in action, but I bet its godawful.  That Necromancer pet put the fear of ... uh well a bony guy with daggers in me.  A nine foot tall giggling bony guy.<br>
